# style
#
# Configure which elements to display in addition to the file contents. 
# The argument is a comma-separated list of components to display (e.g. 'numbers,changes,grid') or a pre-defined style ('full').
# To set a default style, add the '--style=".."' option to the config file or export the BAT_STYLE environment variable (export BAT_STYLE=".."). 
#
# Possible values: *default*, full, auto, plain, changes, header, header-filename, header-filesize, grid, rule, numbers, snip.
#
--style="numbers,changes,header"
